text: Villers-Saint-Frambourg-Ognon is a commune in the Oise department in northern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Villers-Saint-Frambourg (the seat) and Ognon.Arrêté préfectoral 28 September 2018, modified 14 December 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Oise department ==References== Category:Communes of Oise Category:Populated places established in 2019
title: Villers-Saint-Frambourg-Ognon
